  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Finely chop the parsley stalks and pick the leaves. Add a generous glug of olive oil into a large saucepan. Grate the garlic straight into the pan, add in the smoked paprika and parsley stalks. Place on a medium heat, cook stirring for 1 min. Then, add the chopped tomatoes, the butterbeans, and your stock. Let it simmer for 20-25 mins."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Meanwhile, make the flatbreads. Add the self-raising flour and yoghurt into a bowl with 1 tsp of salt. Using your hands, mix together until a dough forms – it will be very sticky so don't worry! Liberally flour a clean surface and portion the dough into 6 balls. Flatten and roll out the balls until 1cm thick, you don't have to be super neat here."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Place a frying pan over high heat, cook the flatbreads in the hot dry pan on both sides until fluffy and golden brown spots appear, 2-4 mins. Transfer to a plate, lightly brush with some olive oil and season with salt. Continue doing this until no more dough is left, stack the flatbreads on top of each other."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "When the stew is done simmering, add in the kale and stir until wilted, 3-5 mins."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Serve the spicy butter bean and kale stew into bowls, top with the remaining yoghurt, and a drizzle of olive oil. Crumble over some feta and finish with a scattering of parsley leaves and a good squeeze of lemon. Serve with a flatbread per person."
    }
  ],
